Name: IMAGERY COVERAGE EXTENT AND MODE
Explanation: DEFINES THE VISIBILITY OF TARGET AND MODE OF COVERAGE.

Name: IMAGE QUALIFIER
Explanation: THE CODE FOR THE RECORDED MEDIA BASED ON THE TYPE OF IMAGERY THAT THE INTERPRETER IS VIEWING VICE THE ORIGINAL FILM NEGATIVE TYPE.

Name: SENSOR TYPE, ALPHABETICAL INDICATOR
Explanation: THE CODE FOR THE TYPE OF IMAGERY SENSOR UTILIZED.

Name: TYPE OF IMAGERY MAPPING
Explanation: THE CODE FOR THE MEDIA OF TRANSMISSION AND QUALITY OF THE PHOTOGRAPHIC PRODUCT.

Name: IMAGE TYPE, ABBREVIATED
Explanation: INDICATES WHICH SENSOR HAS PRODUCED THE IMAGERY.
